CONSENT FORM 


TASK: REIMAGINING AGORA SPACE

Introduction: You are invited to participate in a research study designed to explore the impact of group composition on creativity and communication. Before deciding to participate, it is important for you to understand the nature of the study, its purpose, procedures, potential risks, and benefits.

Purpose of the Study: The purpose of this study is to investigate how different group compositions influence participants' experiences in terms of creativity (innovation) and communication and expression within the group setting.

Risks and Benefits: There are minimal risks associated with this study, such as potential discomfort from sharing personal opinions. However, the benefits include contributing valuable information to the understanding of group dynamics, creativity, and communication.

Confidentiality: Your identity will be kept confidential to the extent permitted by law. Data will be anonymized, and any information that could identify you will be removed from the research findings.

Voluntary Participation: Participation in this study is entirely voluntary. You may withdraw at any time without penalty. Your decision will not affect your relationship with the researchers or your institution.

Informed Consent: By agreeing to participate, you acknowledge that you have read this consent form, had an opportunity to ask questions, and received satisfactory answers. Your consent is voluntary, and you may withdraw at any time without consequence.
